  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Python Object Copying"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Introduction to Copying\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Copying is Needed\n",
    "- To create independent copies of objects\n",
    "- To preserve original data while modifying copies\n",
    "- To avoid unintended side effects\n",
    "- To work with data without affecting the source\n",
    "\n",
    "### Assignment vs Copying\n",
    "- **Assignment**: Creates a new reference to the same object\n",
    "- **Copying**: Creates a new object with the same data\n",
    "- In Python, assignment does NOT create a copy\n",
    "\n",
    "### Reference Behavior in Python\n",
    "- Variables are references to objects in memory\n",
    "- Multiple variables can reference the same object\n",
    "- Modifying through one reference affects all references"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Assignment vs Copying demonstration\n",
    "# Assignment - creates reference\n",
    "original = [1, 2, 3]\n",
    "reference = original\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Reference: {reference}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same object: {original is reference}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Modify through reference\n",
    "reference[0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAfter modifying reference:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")  # Changed!\n",
    "print(f\"Reference: {reference}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Checking object identity\n",
    "a = [1, 2, 3]\n",
    "b = a  # Assignment - same object\n",
    "c = [1, 2, 3]  # New object with same values\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"a is b: {a is b}\")  # True - same object\n",
    "print(f\"a is c: {a is c}\")  # False - different objects\n",
    "print(f\"a == c: {a == c}\")  # True - same values\n",
    "print(f\"id(a): {id(a)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"id(b): {id(b)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"id(c): {id(c)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Shallow Copy\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is Shallow Copy?\n",
    "- Creates a new object\n",
    "- Inserts references to the objects found in the original\n",
    "- Copies the object structure, not the nested objects\n",
    "- Changes to nested objects affect both original and copy\n",
    "\n",
    "### copy.copy() Method\n",
    "- Part of Python's `copy` module\n",
    "- Creates shallow copy of objects\n",
    "- Works on most mutable objects"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import copy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Shallow copy with copy.copy()\n",
    "original = [1, 2, 3]\n",
    "shallow_copy = copy.copy(original)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow copy: {shallow_copy}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same object: {original is shallow_copy}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Modify the copy\n",
    "shallow_copy[0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAfter modifying copy:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")  # Unchanged\n",
    "print(f"Shallow copy: {shallow_copy}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Slicing for Copying\n",
    "- Slicing creates a shallow copy for sequences\n",
    "- `[:]` creates a copy of the entire sequence\n",
    "- Works for lists, strings, tuples"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Shallow copy using slicing\n",
    "original = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "sliced_copy = original[:]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")\n",
    "print(f"Sliced copy: {sliced_copy}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same object: {original is sliced_copy}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "sliced_copy[0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAfter modifying sliced copy:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Sliced copy: {sliced_copy}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Limitations of Shallow Copy\n",
    "- Nested objects are still shared\n",
    "- Modifying nested objects affects both original and copy\n",
    "- Not truly independent for complex data structures"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Shallow copy limitation with nested objects\n",
    "original = [[1, 2], [3, 4]]\n",
    "shallow_copy = copy.copy(original)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow copy: {shallow_copy}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same outer object: {original is shallow_copy}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same inner object: {original[0] is shallow_copy[0]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Modify nested object in copy\n",
    "shallow_copy[0][0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAfter modifying nested object in copy:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")  # Changed!\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow copy: {shallow_copy}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Deep Copy\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is Deep Copy?\n",
    "- Creates a new object\n",
    "- Recursively copies all nested objects\n",
    "- Creates truly independent copies\n",
    "- Changes to nested objects do not affect original\n",
    "\n",
    "### copy.deepcopy() Method\n",
    "- Part of Python's `copy` module\n",
    "- Creates deep copy of objects\n",
    "- Copies all nested objects recursively"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Deep copy with copy.deepcopy()\n",
    "original = [[1, 2], [3, 4]]\n",
    "deep_copy = copy.deepcopy(original)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Deep copy: {deep_copy}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same outer object: {original is deep_copy}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same inner object: {original[0] is deep_copy[0]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Modify nested object in copy\n",
    "deep_copy[0][0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAfter modifying nested object in deep copy:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")  # Unchanged\n",
    "print(f\"Deep copy: {deep_copy}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### When to Use Deep Copy\n",
    "- When you need completely independent copies\n",
    "- When working with nested data structures\n",
    "- When you need to modify copy without affecting original\n",
    "- When caching or memoizing complex objects\n",
    "\n",
    "### Performance Considerations\n",
    "- Deep copy is slower than shallow copy\n",
    "- Uses more memory (creates more objects)\n",
    "- Can be very slow for very large/deep structures\n",
    "- Use shallow copy when possible for performance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "# Performance comparison\n",
    "nested_list = [[i for i in range(100)] for _ in range(100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Shallow copy time\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "shallow = copy.copy(nested_list)\n",
    "shallow_time = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "# Deep copy time\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "deep = copy.deepcopy(nested_list)\n",
    "deep_time = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow copy time: {shallow_time:.6f} seconds\")\n",
    "print(f\"Deep copy time: {deep_time:.6f} seconds\")\n",
    "print(f\"Deep copy is {deep_time/shallow_time:.2f}x slower\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Copying Different Data Types\n",
    "\n",
    "### Lists and Tuples\n",
    "- Lists: mutable, can be copied\n",
    "- Tuples: immutable, copying creates same object (optimization)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Copying lists\n",
    "original_list = [1, 2, 3]\n",
    "list_copy = original_list[:]\n",
    "print(f\"List copy - same object: {original_list is list_copy}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Copying tuples (immutable)\n",
    "original_tuple = (1, 2, 3)\n",
    "tuple_copy = original_tuple[:]\n",
    "print(f\"Tuple copy - same object: {original_tuple is tuple_copy}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Deep copy of tuple with nested mutable objects\n",
    "nested_tuple = ([1, 2], [3, 4])\n",
    "tuple_deep = copy.deepcopy(nested_tuple)\n",
    "print(f\"Nested tuple deep copy - same outer: {nested_tuple is tuple_deep}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Nested tuple deep copy - same inner: {nested_tuple[0] is tuple_deep[0]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Dictionaries\n",
    "- Use `.copy()` method for shallow copy\n",
    "- Use `copy.deepcopy()` for deep copy\n",
    "- Nested dictionaries need deep copy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Copying dictionaries\n",
    "original_dict = {'a': 1, 'b': 2}\n",
    "dict_shallow = original_dict.copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Dict shallow copy - same object: {original_dict is dict_shallow}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Nested dictionary\n",
    "nested_dict = {'outer': {'inner': 1}}\n",
    "nested_shallow = nested_dict.copy()\n",
    "nested_deep = copy.deepcopy(nested_dict)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Nested dict - shallow same outer: {nested_dict is nested_shallow}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Nested dict - shallow same inner: {nested_dict['outer'] is nested_shallow['outer']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Nested dict - deep same inner: {nested_dict['outer'] is nested_deep['outer']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Sets\n",
    "- Use `.copy()` method or `set()` constructor\n",
    "- Sets contain only immutable objects, so shallow copy is usually sufficient"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Copying sets\n",
    "original_set = {1, 2, 3}\n",
    "set_copy = original_set.copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Set copy - same object: {original_set is set_copy}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Alternative method\n",
    "set_copy2 = set(original_set)\n",
    "print(f\"Set copy2 - same object: {original_set is set_copy2}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Custom Objects\n",
    "- Need to implement `__copy__` and `__deepcopy__` methods\n",
    "- Default behavior depends on object's `__dict__`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Copying custom objects\n",
    "class Person:\n",
    "    def __init__(self, name, age):\n",
    "        self.name = name\n",
    "        self.age = age\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __repr__(self):\n",
    "        return f\"Person(name={self.name}, age={self.age})\"\n",
    "\n",
    "person1 = Person(\"Alice\", 25)\n",
    "person2 = copy.copy(person1)\n",
    "person3 = copy.deepcopy(person1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {person1}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow copy: {person2}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Deep copy: {person3}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow same object: {person1 is person2}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Deep same object: {person1 is person3}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Nested Structures\n",
    "- Complex nested structures require deep copy\n",
    "- Shallow copy shares nested objects"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Complex nested structure\n",
    "complex_structure = {\n",
    "    'list': [[1, 2], [3, 4]],\n",
    "    'dict': {'nested': {'value': 10}},\n",
    "    'tuple': ([5, 6], [7, 8])\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "shallow = copy.copy(complex_structure)\n",
    "deep = copy.deepcopy(complex_structure)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Modify nested list in shallow copy\n",
    "shallow['list'][0][0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"Original after shallow modification: {complex_structure}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Modify nested list in deep copy\n",
    "deep['list'][0][0] = 88\n",
    "print(f\"Original after deep modification: {complex_structure}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. The copy Module\n",
    "\n",
    "### copy.copy()\n",
    "- Creates shallow copy\n",
    "- Works on any object that implements `__copy__` or has `__dict__`\n",
    "- Faster than deepcopy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# copy.copy() examples\n",
    "data = [1, 2, [3, 4]]\n",
    "shallow = copy.copy(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {data}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow copy: {shallow}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same object: {data is shallow}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### copy.deepcopy()\n",
    "- Creates deep copy\n",
    "- Recursively copies all nested objects\n",
    "- Handles circular references\n",
    "- Slower but creates truly independent copies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# copy.deepcopy() examples\n",
    "data = [1, 2, [3, 4]]\n",
    "deep = copy.deepcopy(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {data}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Deep copy: {deep}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same object: {data is deep}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Same nested: {data[2] is deep[2]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Custom Copy Methods\n",
    "- `__copy__()`: Define shallow copy behavior\n",
    "- `__deepcopy__()`: Define deep copy behavior\n",
    "- Allows control over how objects are copied"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Custom copy methods\n",
    "class CustomObject:\n",
    "    def __init__(self, data):\n",
    "        self.data = data\n",
    "        self.metadata = \"original\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __copy__(self):\n",
    "        # Custom shallow copy\n",
    "        new_obj = CustomObject(self.data)\n",
    "        new_obj.metadata = \"shallow_copy\"\n",
    "        return new_obj\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __deepcopy__(self, memo):\n",
    "        # Custom deep copy\n",
    "        new_obj = CustomObject(copy.deepcopy(self.data, memo))\n",
    "        new_obj.metadata = \"deep_copy\"\n",
    "        return new_obj\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __repr__(self):\n",
    "        return f\"CustomObject(data={self.data}, metadata={self.metadata})\"\n",
    "\n",
    "original = CustomObject([1, 2, 3])\n",
    "shallow = copy.copy(original)\n",
    "deep = copy.deepcopy(original)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {original}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shallow: {shallow}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Deep: {deep}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Practical Examples\n",
    "\n",
    "### Copying Nested Lists\n",
    "Demonstrating the difference between shallow and deep copy with nested lists."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Copying nested lists\n",
    "matrix = [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6], [7, 8, 9]]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Shallow copy\n",
    "matrix_shallow = copy.copy(matrix)\n",
    "matrix_shallow[0][0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"After shallow copy modification:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {matrix}\")  # Changed!\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reset and try deep copy\n",
    "matrix = [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6], [7, 8, 9]]\n",
    "matrix_deep = copy.deepcopy(matrix)\n",
    "matrix_deep[0][0] = 99\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAfter deep copy modification:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original: {matrix}\")  # Unchanged\n",
    "print(f"Deep copy: {matrix_deep}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Copying Dictionaries with Objects\n",
    "Copying dictionaries that contain objects as values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Copying dictionaries with objects\n",
    "class Item:\n",
    "    def __init__(self, name, price):\n",
    "        self.name = name\n",
    "        self.price = price\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __repr__(self):\n",
    "        return f\"Item({self.name}, ${self.price})\"\n",
    "\n",
    "cart = {\n",
    "    'item1': Item('Apple', 1.99),\n",
    "    'item2': Item('Banana', 0.99)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Shallow copy\n",
    "cart_shallow = cart.copy()\n",
    "cart_shallow['item1'].price = 2.99\n",
    "print(f\"Original after shallow: {cart}\")  # Changed!\n",
    "\n",
    "# Deep copy\n",
    "cart = {\n",
    "    'item1': Item('Apple', 1.99),\n",
    "    'item2': Item('Banana', 0.99)\n",
    "}\n",
    "cart_deep = copy.deepcopy(cart)\n",
    "cart_deep['item1'].price = 2.99\n",
    "print(f\"Original after deep: {cart}\")  # Unchanged\n",
    "print(f"Deep copy: {cart_deep}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Independent Copies vs References\n",
    "Understanding when you need independent copies vs when references are sufficient."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# When to use references (assignment)\n",
    "shared_config = {'debug': True, 'version': '1.0'}\n",
    "config_ref = shared_config  # Intentionally share\n",
    "config_ref['debug'] = False\n",
    "print(f\"Shared config: {shared_config}\")  # Both see the change\n",
    "\n",
    "# When to use copies (independent)\n",
    "base_config = {'debug': True, 'version': '1.0'}\n",
    "user_config = copy.deepcopy(base_config)  # Independent\n",
    "user_config['debug'] = False\n",
    "print(f\"Base config: {base_config}\")  # Unchanged\n",
    "print(f\"User config: {user_config}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Performance Comparison\n",
    "Comparing shallow and deep copy performance with different data structures."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test with simple list\n",
    "simple_list = list(range(10000))\n",
    "\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "for _ in range(1000):\n",
    "    copy.copy(simple_list)\n",
    "shallow_simple = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "for _ in range(1000):\n",
    "    copy.deepcopy(simple_list)\n",
    "deep_simple = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Simple list - Shallow: {shallow_simple:.4f}s, Deep: {deep_simple:.4f}s\")\n",
    "print(f\"Ratio: {deep_simple/shallow_simple:.2f}x\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test with nested structure\n",
    "nested = [[i for i in range(100)] for _ in range(100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "for _ in range(100):\n",
    "    copy.copy(nested)\n",
    "shallow_nested = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "for _ in range(100):\n",
    "    copy.deepcopy(nested)\n",
    "deep_nested = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nNested list - Shallow: {shallow_nested:.4f}s, Deep: {deep_nested:.4f}s\")\n",
    "print(f\"Ratio: {deep_nested/shallow_nested:.2f}x\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Key Points & Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "### Shallow vs Deep Copy Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "| Feature | Shallow Copy | Deep Copy |\n",
    "|---------|--------------|----------|\n",
    "| **Creates new object** | Yes | Yes |\n",
    "| **Copies nested objects** | No (shares references) | Yes (creates new) |\n",
    "| **Performance** | Fast | Slower |\n",
    "| **Memory usage** | Less | More |\n",
    "| **Independence** | Partial (nested shared) | Complete |\n",
    "| **Method** | `copy.copy()` or slicing | `copy.deepcopy()` |\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Use Shallow Copy\n",
    "✅ Simple data structures (no nesting)\n",
    "✅ When you want to share nested objects\n",
    "✅ When performance is critical\n",
    "✅ When nested objects are immutable\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Use Deep Copy\n",
    "✅ Nested data structures\n",
    "✅ When you need complete independence\n",
    "✅ When modifying copy shouldn't affect original\n",
    "✅ When caching or memoizing\n",
    "\n",
    "### Copy Methods Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "| Data Type | Shallow Copy | Deep Copy |\n",
    "|-----------|--------------|----------|\n",
    "| **List** | `list.copy()`, slicing, `copy.copy()` | `copy.deepcopy()` |\n",
    "| **Dict** | `dict.copy()`, `copy.copy()` | `copy.deepcopy()` |\n",
    "| **Set** | `set.copy()`, `copy.copy()` | `copy.deepcopy()` |\n",
    "| **Tuple** | Slicing (may return same object) | `copy.deepcopy()` |\n",
    "| **Custom Object** | `copy.copy()` | `copy.deepcopy()` |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Takeaways\n",
    "- Assignment creates references, not copies\n",
    "- Shallow copy creates new object but shares nested objects\n",
    "- Deep copy creates completely independent copies\n",
    "- Use shallow copy for simple structures and performance\n",
    "- Use deep copy for nested structures and independence\n",
    "- The `copy` module provides both `copy()` and `deepcopy()` functions\n",
    "- Custom objects can define `__copy__` and `__deepcopy__` methods\n",
    "- Understanding the difference prevents unintended side effects\n",
    "- Choose the right copy method based on your use case"
